{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891063389,"sessionID":"ses_284a536feffe5RcNTMgqkoHvaO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5b1d8a0015tZ1xi6oUmC4Oq","messageID":"msg_d7b5b1033001jtvW2IXG3oZDsZ","sessionID":"ses_284a536feffe5RcNTMgqkoHvaO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_54c88fc329e74c60b796befc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK\n2: \n3: Python SDK for invoking Agent Runtime workloads in the AgentCube platform.\n4: \n5: ## Installation\n6: \n7: Install from source:\n8: \n9: ```bash\n10: cd sdk-python\n11: pip install .\n12: ```\n13: \n14: Install with development dependencies:\n15: \n16: ```bash\n17: pip install -e \".[dev]\"\n18: ```\n19: \n20: ## Requirements\n21: \n22: - Python 3.10+\n23: - requests >= 2.28.0\n24: - urllib3 >= 1.26.0\n25: \n26: ## Quick Start\n27: \n28: ### Basic Usage\n29: \n30: The recommended way to use `AgentRuntimeClient` is with the context manager pattern:\n31: \n32: ```python\n33: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n34: \n35: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n36:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n37:     namespace=\"default\",\n38:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n39: ) as client:\n40:     response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n41:     print(response)\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Environment Variable Configuration\n45: \n46: You can set the `ROUTER_URL` environment variable instead of providing it explicitly:\n47: \n48: ```bash\n49: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ```python\n53: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n54: \n55: # router_url will be read from ROUTER_URL environment variable\n56: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n57:     agent_name=\"my-agent\"\n58: ) as client:\n59:     response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n60:     print(response)\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Explicit Session ID\n64: \n65: To reuse an existing session instead of bootstrapping a new one:\n66: \n67: ```python\n68: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n69: \n70: # Bootstrap a session first\n71: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n72:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n73:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n74: ) as client1:\n75:     session_id = client1.session_id\n76: \n77: # Reuse the session in another client\n78: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n79:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n80:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n81:     session_id=session_id  # Skip bootstrap\n82: ) as client2:\n83:     response = client2.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n84:     print(response)\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ## API Reference\n88: \n89: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n90: \n91: High-level client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads.\n92: \n93: #### Constructor\n94: \n95: ```python\n96: AgentRuntimeClient(\n97:     agent_name: str,\n98:     namespace: str = \"default\",\n99:     router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n100:     verbose: bool = False,\n101:     session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n102:     timeout: int = 120,\n103:     connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n104: )\n105: ```\n106: \n107: **Parameters:**\n108: - `agent_name` (str): Name of the target agent runtime\n109: - `namespace` (str): Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n110: - `router_url` (Optional[str]): Router base URL. Resolves from argument or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n111: - `verbose` (bool): Enable debug logging (default: False)\n112: - `session_id` (Optional[str]): Existing session ID. If None, bootstraps new session\n113: - `timeout` (int): Default request timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n114: - `connect_timeout` (float): Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n115: \n116: **Raises:**\n117: - `ValueError`: If router_url not provided and ROUTER_URL env var not set\n118: \n119: #### Methods\n120: \n121: ##### invoke(payload, timeout=None)\n122: \n123: Invoke the agent runtime with a JSON payload.\n124: \n125: ```python\n126: response = client.invoke({\n127:     \"action\": \"query\",\n128:     \"parameters\": {\"key\": \"value\"}\n129: })\n130: ```\n131: \n132: **Parameters:**\n133: - `payload` (Dict[str, Any]): JSON-serializable dict to send to the agent\n134: - `timeout` (Optional[float]): Optional per-call timeout override in seconds\n135: \n136: **Returns:**\n137: - Parsed JSON response from the agent\n138: \n139: **Raises:**\n140: - `ValueError`: If session_id is not initialized\n141: \n142: ##### close()\n143: \n144: Close the underlying HTTP session.\n145: \n146: ```python\n147: client.close()\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **Note:** When using the context manager pattern, `close()` is called automatically.\n151: \n152: #### Context Manager Support\n153: \n154: `AgentRuntimeClient` supports the context manager protocol for automatic resource cleanup:\n155: \n156: ```python\n157: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n158:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n159:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n160: ) as client:\n161:     response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n162: # client.close() is called automatically\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n166: \n167: Low-level HTTP client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n168: \n169: ```python\n170: from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n171: \n172: client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n173:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n174:     namespace=\"default\",\n175:     agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n176: )\n177: \n178: # Bootstrap a session\n179: session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n180: \n181: # Invoke with payload\n182: response = client.invoke(\n183:     session_id=session_id,\n184:     payload={\"message\": \"hello\"}\n185: )\n186: \n187: client.close()\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ## Configuration\n191: \n192: ### Environment Variables\n193: \n194: | Variable | Description | Required |\n195: |----------|-------------|----------|\n196: | `ROUTER_URL` | Router base URL for Agent Runtime | Yes (if not provided to constructor) |\n197: \n198: ### Timeout Configuration\n199: \n200: The SDK uses separate timeouts for connection and read operations:\n201: \n202: - **Connection timeout**: 5.0 seconds (default)\n203: - **Read timeout**: 120 seconds (default)\n204: \n205: You can override the read timeout per-call:\n206: \n207: ```python\n208: response = client.invoke(payload, timeout=60)  # 60 second read timeout\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ### Logging\n212: \n213: Enable verbose logging to see debug messages:\n214: \n215: ```python\n216: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n217:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n218:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n219:     verbose=True  # Enable DEBUG level logging\n220: )\n221: ```\n222: \n223: ## Examples\n224: \n225: See the `examples/` directory for complete working examples:\n226: \n227: - `examples/agent_runtime_basic.py` - Basic usage with context manager\n228: - `examples/agent_runtime_explicit_session.py` - Explicit session ID management\n229: \n230: ## Running Tests\n231: \n232: ### Unit Tests\n233: \n234: ```bash\n235: cd sdk-python\n236: pytest tests/unit/ -v\n237: ```\n238: \n239: ### Integration Tests\n240: \n241: Integration tests require a running Router instance:\n242: \n243: ```bash\n244: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:8080\"\n245: export TEST_AGENT_NAME=\"test-agent\"\n246: pytest tests/integration/ -v\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ### Test with Coverage\n250: \n251: ```bash\n252: pytest --cov=agentcube tests/ -v\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ### Type Checking\n256: \n257: ```bash\n258: mypy agentcube/\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Linting\n262: \n263: ```bash\n264: ruff check agentcube/\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ## Error Handling\n268: \n269: The SDK raises the following exceptions:\n270: \n271: | Exception | Condition |\n272: |-----------|-----------|\n273: | `ValueError` | Missing router_url (neither argument nor env var) |\n274: | `ValueError` | Bootstrap response lacks session header |\n275: | `ValueError` | invoke() called without initialized session_id |\n276: | `requests.HTTPError` | Server returns HTTP error status |\n277: | `requests.RequestException` | Network errors |\n278: \n279: Example error handling:\n280: \n281: ```python\n282: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n283: import requests\n284: \n285: try:\n286:     with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\") as client:\n287:         response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n288: except ValueError as e:\n289:     print(f\"Configuration error: {e}\")\n290: except requests.HTTPError as e:\n291:     print(f\"HTTP error: {e}\")\n292: except requests.RequestException as e:\n293:     print(f\"Network error: {e}\")\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ## Architecture\n297: \n298: ```\n299: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n300: │       AgentRuntimeClient                │\n301: │  (High-level Facade)                    │\n302: │  - agent_name                           │\n303: │  - namespace                            │\n304: │  - session_id (bootstrapped or given)   │\n305: │  - dp_client                            │\n306: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n307:                      │\n308:                      │ delegates to\n309:                      ▼\n310: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n311: │   AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient           │\n312: │  (HTTP Client for Router)               │\n313: │  - base_url                             │\n314: │  - session (requests.Session)           │\n315: │  - timeout / connect_timeout            │\n316: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ## License\n320: \n321: Apache License 2.0\n322: \n323: ## Contributing\n324: \n325: Contributions are welcome! Please read our contributing guidelines before submitting pull requests.\n326: \n327: ## Support\n328: \n329: For issues and feature requests, please file an issue on the GitHub repository.\n\n(End of file - total 329 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK\n\nPython SDK for invoking Agent Runtime workloads in the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall from source:\n\n```bash\ncd sdk-python\npip install .\n```\n\nInstall with development dependencies:\n\n```bash\npip install -e \".[dev]\"\n```\n\n## Requirements","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/README.md","time":{"start":1775891063372,"end":1775891063387}}}}
